ZH: 他们排成一排等待进入电影院。
EN: They lined up to enter the movie theater.

ZH: 我们排队等着买火车票。
EN: We queued up to buy train tickets.

ZH: 学生们在操场上排着队做晨操。
EN: The students lined up on the playground to do morning exercises.

ZH: 请你排队等候乘坐电梯。
EN: Please queue up and wait to take the elevator.

ZH: 老师让学生们排好队上课。
EN: The teacher asked the students to line up for class.

ZH: 我们排在第三位，等待机会。
EN: We were in third place in line, waiting for our turn.

ZH: 他们排着队向山顶前进。
EN: They lined up and moved towards the mountaintop.

ZH: 人群中排起一股莫名的气氛。
EN: A strange atmosphere arose among the crowd.

ZH: 长队沿着街道排成长龙。
EN: A long line stretched along the street like a dragon.

ZH: 整齐的排列是训练出的美德。
EN: Neat arrangement is a cultivated virtue.

ZH: 妈妈在柜子里把碗碟排整齐。
EN: Mom neatly arranged the plates and dishes in the cupboard.

ZH: 队伍排得整整齐齐，有秩序。
EN: The team lined up neatly and in order.

ZH: 小朋友们排着队去参观动物园。
EN: The children lined up to visit the zoo.

ZH: 请大家排队等候进入展览馆。
EN: Please line up and wait to enter the exhibition hall.

ZH: 士兵们排成一排迎接国王的到来。
EN: The soldiers lined up to welcome the arrival of the king.

ZH: 乘客们有秩序地排成一排登机。
EN: The passengers lined up in an orderly manner to board the plane.

ZH: 在超市门口排队购买新鲜蔬菜。
EN: Queue up at the supermarket entrance to buy fresh vegetables.

ZH: 餐桌上的盘子被整整齐齐地排列着。
EN: The plates on the dining table were neatly arranged.

ZH: 哥哥和弟弟排在前面一起参加比赛。
EN: The older brother and younger brother competed together at the front.

ZH: 请大家按照座位号排队入场。
EN: Please enter according to your seat number and line up.
